The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Digvijay, Pilot held
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Digvijay, Pilot held
                            
	Lucknow, July 29: Mayavatis police today arrested Congress leaders Digvijay Singh, Sachin Pilot and Rita Bahuguna Joshi while they were going to a farmers rally against land acquisition in Badalpur, the Uttar Pradesh chief ministers native village.        
	The village in Gautambudhnagar district  another name for Noida  is in western Uttar Pradesh.         
	The Mayavati government wants to make an amusement park after acquiring land in four villages  Badalpur being one of them. The total area to be acquired is 920996.3 acres.                                                                                                                                                                         
